verses.text:
So, Son of man, prophesy;
\q2 clap your hands to show that you are very sad about what is going to happen.
\q1 My sword will strike my people again and again;
\q1 it is a sword for slaughtering many people,
\q2 while I attack them from every side.
\q1

Then I will clap my hands triumphantly;
\q2 and then I will no longer be angry.
\q1 That will surely happen because I, Yahweh, have said it.'"

But now everyone living along the coast is terrified because the enemy has destroyed the great city.
\q2 It is as though the land along the coast itself were trembling;
\q1 the people on the islands in the sea are terrified because that city exists no more.'

You made the sails from fine embroidered linen from Egypt;
\q2 those sails were like flags that people could see far away.
\q1

Men from the cities of Sidon and Arvad pulled your oars;
\q2 the men who steered the ship were experienced sailors from Tyre.
\q1

Men from the cities of Arvad and Helech were watchmen on your city walls;
\q2 men from the city of Gammad were in your towers.
\q1 They also hung their shields on your walls;
\q2 they also made your city very beautiful.

Merchants came to you from the island of Rhodes.
\q1 People from many nations by the sea traded with you;
\q2 they brought ivory and valuable black ebony wood to trade for things that you had.

Cargo ships from Tarshish carried all those things that you sold;
\q2 the warehouses on your island were full of all those things and brought you great honor.
\q1

All the men who pulled the oars will leave the ships;
\q2 the sailors and pilots will come to the shore and stand on the beach.
\q1

Because you were wise and shrewd in business, you have become very rich;
\q2 you have acquired much gold and silver for your treasuries.
\q1
